BaseField.Name: Label99
BaseField.Text: Instructions Enter a list of tokens, comma separated that describe content which will need to be manually entered at the time of letter generation rather than lookup in the system. Manual tokens must have curly brackets surrounding them e.g. {Administrative Penalty Amount}

BaseField.Name: DataField1
BaseField.Text: Instructions Tokens are pieces of information that will dynamically change in the Subject or Body of a letter. In order to add a token, put the bracket [] symbols in the text where you want the token to display. Inside of the brackets [] add the token name listed below to display that data. For example, if [First Name] is listed below, you could write, "Hello [First Name]," to address the email recipient by their first name.
